description._content: Catalog #: 09_01586 Title: Elwyn H. Gibbon Special Collection Photo Hankow China Additional Information: Elwyn Gibbon in winter gear at Hankow 1938 with Douglas O-2M aircraft in background, Elwyn Gibbon (b.1911 d.1942) was an American pilot who served as a pilot in the Chinese Air Force in the Foreign Volunteer Squadron. Later he served as a Vultee Aircraft Company test pilot in Karachi, India, where he died in a plane crash in 1942. Corporation Name: Douglas Aircraft Company Tags: Elwyn H.
